article.headline: Middle Tennessee 77, Tennessee St. 62
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Jimmy Oden scored 14 points from the bench, hitting 11 of 12 free throws, to lead Middle Tennessee past Tennessee State 77-62 on Thursday night. Middle Tennessee (7-1) got 33 points from its bench in the winning effort compared to just 11 points for Tennessee State. The Blue Raiders trailed by one, 44-43, before going on a 15-5 run over the next seven minutes to take a 58-49 lead with 5:38 left to play. Middle Tennessee would not relinquish the lead, pushing its advantage to 13, 73-60, behind two Oden free throws. Oden sank 10 free throws during the final 1:45 of the second half. Jason Jones and Marcus Knight each scored 12 points and James Gallman added 10 for the Blue Raiders. Patrick Miller led Tennessee State (3-5) with 14 points. Robert Covington added 12 and Kellen Thornton chipped in with 11 for the Tigers.
